article.headline: Tenn.-Martin 91, Tennessee St. 81
article.story: MARTIN, Tenn. (AP) -- Lester Hudson scored 38 points as Tennessee-Martin beat Tennessee State 91-80 on Thursday. Hudson hit 12-of-21 from the floor and 10-of-11 free throws as the Skyhawks (12-14, 8-8 Ohio Valley Conference) pulled away in the second half. Tennessee State (10-14, 7-8) trailed 44-40 at the half and fell behind by as much as 12 after the break. Tennessee-Martin also got 18 points from Gerald Robinson and Marquis Weddle. Tennessee State was led by Bruce Price with 24 points, 21 points by Gerald Robinson Jr. and 12 points by LaDarious Weaver. The Skyhawks made 21-of-26 free throws to 9-of-13 for Tennessee State.
